cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DM, cs.IT, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with domain theory, functional analysis, and algebraic structures related to probability and nondeterminism. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is a likely category as the paper deals with characterizing mixed powerdomains as free algebras for suitable (in)equation-al theories. cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a likely category as the paper deals with functional representation theorems and equivalencies between state transformers and predicate transformers. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a possible category as the paper deals with convex sets of subprobability valuations. cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possible category as the paper deals with truth-values and probabilistic algebras. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with combining different forms of nondeterminism.
